Catalyst-Plugin-EnvironmentDetector version 0.01
================================================

A plugin to allow defining an arbitrary environment 
keyword tied to hostname or environment variables and
matching based on a regex pattern. Typical use would be
to detect the difference between a 'test' and 'production'
environment from within your Catalyst application. 

INSTALLATION

To install this module type the following:

   perl Makefile.PL
   make
   make test
   make install

DEPENDENCIES

    Sys::Hostname

